---
title: All Kale Chicken Caesar with Tomato, Croutons & Parmesan
description: No disrespect to the classic chicken Caesar, but this version with kale is truly next-level. We massage the leaves with a simple lemon and olive oil dressing until the greens are tender and full of flavor, then toss with crunchy croutons, rich, salty Parm, tomato wedges, and creamy, tangy Caesar dressing. It’s all topped with slices of herb-seared chicken for a hearty-yet-light-feeling dinner you’re going to want to make again and again.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/all-kale-chicken-caesar-f4e08fd4.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/all-kale-chicken-caesar-5fc6c77ced262d664a13aa24-e53cf868.pdf
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 520 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 22 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 720 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/all-kale-chicken-caesar-5fc6c77ced262d664a13aa24
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry all produce. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Cut @roma tomato{1} into wedges.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Caesar dressing{1.5%ounce}, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, lemon zest, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}; set aside.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{}.

Meanwhile, remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}. Add to a #large bowl{} along with a large drizzle of olive oil, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a big pinch of @salt{}.

Using your hands, massage kale (similar to how you would knead dough) until leaves are tender, ~{1%minute}.

> Don't skip this step—massaging helps the kale leaves wilt slightly, giving them a tender (never fibrous!) texture.

Add tomato, @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}, @croutons{1}, and 2/3 of the dressing (save the rest for serving) to bowl with kale.

Gently toss until coated. Season with salt, pepper, and more lemon juice if desired.

Divide salad between shallow #bowls{} or #plates{}. Slice chicken crosswise and arrange over salad. Drizzle with remaining dressing and serve.